SIMPLE: populous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Populous
<hw>Pop"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>populosus</ets>, fr. <ets>populus</ets> people: cf. F.
<ets>populeux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding in people; full
of inhabitants; containing many inhabitants in proportion to the extent
of the country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heaven, yet <qex>populous</qex>, retains⟦br⟧
Number sufficient to possess her realms.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Popular; famous.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>J. Webster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Common; vulgar.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Arden of Feversham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Numerous; in large number.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧The dust . . . raised by your <xex>populous</xex> troops.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pop"u*lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Pop"u*lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poraille</ent>⟦br⟧
